commit.message:
Add datacompy[spark] pip install option (#54)

* Update copyright to 2020

* Use Python 3.7 for stuff

* black reformatting of test_sparkcompare.py

* Add spark as "extras" requirements in setup.py

This allows a user to `pip install datacompy[spark]` and be ready to use Spark comparison out of the box.

Also:
* Revert #38 as Python 2.7 support has been dropped
* Link setup.py "install_requires" to requirements.txt to avoid any chance of them getting misaligned

* Use union to remove unionAll deprecation warning

* Change more unionAlls to unions

* Optimize imports

* Pretty-up a couple questionable decisions by black

* Bump Travis dist to xenial

This should hopefully have Python 3.5, 3.6, and 3.7 binaries to test on.

* Try to use Java 8

* Another shot at trying to use Java 8 on xenial
